From 8a812655325cad635b14c72d68c9b9f719124fe5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sean Smith <DefendTheDisabled@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 15:58:05 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 04/16] btrfs: add ptime field to btrfs_inode_item on-disk
 layout
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Consumes 16 bytes of the existing reserved[4] region in struct
btrfs_inode_item: 12 bytes for struct btrfs_timespec ptime (same
encoding as atime/mtime/ctime/otime — __le64 sec + __le32 nsec)
plus 4 bytes for __reserved_pad to maintain 8-byte alignment of
the remaining reserved[2].

The on-disk layout change is:
    struct btrfs_timespec ctime;
    struct btrfs_timespec otime;
-   __le64 reserved[4];
+   struct btrfs_timespec ptime;
+   __le32 __reserved_pad;
+   __le64 reserved[2];

Backward compatibility is maintained — old kernels reading the
inode see zeros in the ptime field and pass them through
unchanged. When an unpatched kernel RW-mounts a filesystem with
ptime-populated inodes, it would silently drop ptime on inode
updates. The BTRFS_FEATURE_COMPAT_RO_PTIME feature flag (next
commit) prevents this at mount time.

This is the on-disk layout commit. In-memory representation and
read/write paths come in following commits.

Ref: Decision #44 (Btrfs is native ptime FS with separate field)
Ref: Decision #49 (native vs mapped ptime architecture)
Files: include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h (struct btrfs_inode_item)
---
 include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h b/include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h
index fc29d273845d..719c00363088 100644
--- a/include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h
+++ b/include/uapi/linux/btrfs_tree.h
@@ -890,7 +890,9 @@ struct btrfs_inode_item {
 	 * a little future expansion, for more than this we can
 	 * just grow the inode item and version it
 	 */
-	__le64 reserved[4];
+	struct btrfs_timespec ptime;
+	__le32 __reserved_pad;
+	__le64 reserved[2];
 	struct btrfs_timespec atime;
 	struct btrfs_timespec ctime;
 	struct btrfs_timespec mtime;
-- 
